                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 151.07/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nogales</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American Consul at Mazatlan telegraphs that the Chinese colony, consisting of
                    four hundred residents, may be compelled to leave Mexico and asks whether
                    permission could be granted for temporary residence, as an act of humanity, at
                    San Francisco or San Diego.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dye.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
